column1: In the early years the gauge was rarely read. Although there were attempts to split them into months from referencing the Cowsic Valley station I am quoting the values as originally given
The values in 1903 are not bracketed, but are similar to the readings which are bracketed, so given as such
Annual values rejected from survey map 1929
Actual location of gauge not known - judged to be on same side of moor as its New Location which is known, and this is near the trail
